Shapiro-Wilk normality test

2012 sample size is <30 (n=28)

## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  ivee_2012_3$SIZE
## W = 0.81375, p-value = 0.0003044

p-value = 0.0003044

RESULT:
From the output, the p-value (3.044364910^{-4}) < 0.05 implying that the distribution of the data are significantly different from normal distribution. In other words, we cannot assume the normality, and will have to use Welchs t-test.

T-test

## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  ivee_2012_3$SIZE and ivee_2017_3$SIZE

## sample estimates:
## mean of x mean of y 
##  66.07692  71.45215

RESULT:
Mean Lobster Sizes differ significantly between the 2012 and 2017 at IVEE at the 0.05 confidence level. (t(28.09) = -2.2, p = 0.0360973).
